properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 11 at 10:59AM PST until February 11 at 11:21AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Cedar River At Renton affecting King County
Cedar River Near Landsburg affecting King County

Rivers will continue to recede today with just light rain expected.
Dry day on Wednesday will allow rivers to keep receding.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Cedar River Near Landsburg
* Until this morning.
* At 10:00 AM Tuesday the stage was 5.5 feet.
* Flood stage is 5.7 feet.
* Fell below flood stage early this morning.
* No additional flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river fell below flood stage at  2:45 AM Tuesday and
will continue to fall. Flooding will continue in some areas until
the flood wave has completely passed downstream.
* Impact...At 5.0 feet, the Cedar River will flood low areas from
Landsburg downstream through Maplewood, mainly in Dorre Don area of
Maple Valley and along Jones Rd.  A stage of 5.0 feet on the Cedar
River corresponds roughly to a phase 3 flood in the King County
flood system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
